Text.Value: Who were you before you became a slave to the Absolute?
Your... failure... gives... my death... meaning...
Soon to lose... job... to... Steel Watch...
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
Lewis... Morell... loyal servant... of the... Absolute...
Why did you join the Absolute's forces?
Many came... few left... men slaughtered...
And in the end, did you find your purpose with the Absolute?
*The corpse seems willing to speak - but not to its killer.*
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
How many more cultists are there?
Felled... on the threshold... of victory...
Where were these sewers you came through?

Synopsis: A dead absolutist outside a civilian home. He is present to give the player an indication of how difficult a frontal assault may be. There may also be a subtle hint at a path the absolutist took to make it to High Hall in the first place.
